ng-distance pilot: reliability, decision-making, calm under pressure, teamwork, communication, professional development.\n\nCandidate A: strong leadership, anticipation, spatial vision, but show-off and not open to new ideas may hinder crew cooperation and adaptability.\n\nCandidate B: conscientious, stress handling, weather assessment, computer skills, but nasty remarks and weak number memory could be safety risk.\n\nCandidate C: quick correct decisions, calm, tech understanding, but communication issues, egocentric, unwilling to develop.\n\nCandidate D: problem solving, responsibility, concentration, handles unexpected, but hot temper and know-it-all may affect crew.\n\nWhich is best? Need to weigh seriousness. For safety, communication and teamwork are critical. Candidate B's nasty remarks could be severe. Candidate C's communication difficulty also serious. Candidate D's hot temper also serious. Candidate A's show-off and not open to new ideas also problematic but perhaps less severe? Show-off may affect crew morale; not open to new ideas could hinder learning.\n\nConsidering overall, Candidate A has strong technical and leadership, and attitude issues but maybe manageable. Candidate B's memory weakness for numbers could affect navigation; nasty remarks could degrade crew. Candidate C's egocentric and unwillingness to develop is concerning for long-term. Candidate D's hot temper could cause conflict under stress.\n\nThus provisional preference: Candidate A.\n\nWe should note uncertainties: need more info on how severe the show-off behavior is, and whether not open to new ideas impacts safety. Also want to know if any other agents have additional positive/negative info.\n\nThus produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE summarizing.\n\nMETADATA vote: Candidate A."}
