nd \"eats unhealthily\". Those are negative for teamwork and health.\n\nCandidate B: positives: very conscientious, handles stress well, good at assessing weather, excellent computer skills. Negatives: weak memory for numbers, makes nasty remarks, pretentious, wrong tone, possibly \"uncooperative\". Also \"unfriendly\"? Not listed but similar.\n\nCandidate C: positives: 100% reliable, creates positive atmosphere with crew, quick correct decisions, calm in crisis, understands complicated technology, excellent attention skills, puts concern for others above everything. Negatives: difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric, not willing to further education.\n\nCandidate D: positives: responds adequately to unexpected events, concentrates well, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously. Negatives: hot temper, know-it-all, moody, loner, weak leadership.\n\nNow weigh criteria: reliability, technical competence, calmness, decision-making, teamwork/communication, professional development.\n\nReliability: C is 100% reliable. A no explicit reliability. B conscientious but no reliability statement. D no reliability.\n\nTechnical competence: A (anticipation, spatial vision, complex connections) strong. B (weather assessment, computer skills) good. C (understands complicated technology, excellent attention) good. D (problem solving, concentration) good.\n\nCalmness/decision-making: C (quick correct decisions, calm in crisis). A not mentioned. B handles stress well. D responds adequately to unexpected events.\n\nTeamwork/communication: C creates positive atmosphere but difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric. A has leadership but show-off, not open to new ideas, not good at criticism. B makes nasty remarks, pretentious, wrong tone. D hot temper, know-it-all, loner.\n\nProfessional development: A not open to new ideas. B maybe okay. C not willing to further education. D maybe okay.\n\nOverall, C seems strongest on reliability, crew atmosphere, decision-making, calmness, technical competence, but has communication difficulty and egocentric attitude. A has strong technical and leadership but attitude issues and lack of reliability evidence. B has good stress handling but interpersonal issues and numeric memory. D has problem solving but temperament.\n\nThus I think C is best overall. So I should update my vote to Candidate C. Provide reasoning, mention others' votes, tradeoffs, uncertainties, what would change my vote.\n\nNow produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE and METADATA_JSON with vote Candidate C."}
